### Render Availability Settings Atom in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/atoms/availability-settings.mdx

Renders the core AvailabilitySettings atom using React. It includes callbacks for update success, delete success, and form state changes, allowing integration with application logic. The atom manages user-defined available time slots.

```javascript
import { AvailabilitySettings } from "@calcom/atoms";

export default function Availability() {
  return (
    <>
       <AvailabilitySettings
          onUpdateSuccess={() => {
            console.log("Updated schedule successfully");
          }}
          onDeleteSuccess={() => {
            console.log("Deleted schedule successfully");
          }}
          onFormStateChange={(formState) => {
            console.log("Form state updated");
            // Access form data: formState.name, formState.schedule, formState.timeZone, etc.
          }}
       />
    </>
  )
}
```

