### Render Conferencing Apps Atom Component in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/atoms/conferencing-apps.mdx

This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to render the ConferencingAppsSettings Atom component from '@calcom/atoms'. It constructs a callback URI using the current window's origin and path, passing it as props to the component. This setup is essential for handling installation redirects and error handling within the Cal.com conferencing app integration.

```javascript
import { ConferencingAppsSettings } from "@calcom/atoms";
import { usePathname } from "next/navigation";

export default function ConferencingApps() {
  const pathname = usePathname();
  const callbackUri = `${window.location.origin}${pathname}`;

  return (
    <>
        <ConferencingAppsSettings returnTo={callbackUri} onErrorReturnTo={callbackUri} />
    </>
  )
}
```

