### Customize Complex Atom with customClassNames and Callbacks

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/quickstart.mdx

This example shows advanced customization of a complex Cal.com atom, `AvailabilitySettings`. It utilizes `customClassNames` to style specific internal elements like subtitles and headings. Additionally, it demonstrates how to hook into events like `onUpdateSuccess`, `onUpdateError`, `onDeleteError`, and `onDeleteSuccess` with provided callback functions.

```javascript
<AvailabilitySettings
  customClassNames={{
    subtitlesClassName: "text-red-500",
    ctaClassName: "border p-4 rounded-md",
    editableHeadingClassName: "underline font-semibold",
  }}
  onUpdateSuccess={() => {
    console.log("Updated successfully");
  }}
  onUpdateError={() => {
    console.log("update error");
  }}
  onDeleteError={() => {
    console.log("delete error");
  }}
  onDeleteSuccess={() => {
    console.log("Deleted successfully");
  }}
/>;
```

